\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 Drawing Lewis structures
\f1\b0\fs36 \cf0 \
\
1. Count the total number of valence electrons.\
\
2. Position the atoms according to their arrangement in the molecule or polyatomic ion (if uncertain, make the more electronegative atoms outer atoms).\
\
3. Join atoms by a single line representing two bonding electrons.\
\
4. Distribute the remaining electrons on the outer atoms (other than hydrogen) until they each have an octet.\
\
5. Place the remaining electrons at the central atom.\
\
6. Complete octets at any atoms (other than hydrogen) which do not have eight electrons, by forming multiple bonds using nonbonding pairs from adjacent atoms.\
\
\
