\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 Assigning formal charge
\f1\b0\fs36 \cf0 \
\
The charge at an atom in a Lewis structure indicates whether the bonded atom is more positive or negative than the isolated atom. The sum of formal charges equals the overall charge on the species.\
\
After drawing up the Lewis structure, count the number of electrons surrounding each atom (a bond indicates one electron for the atom). If the number of electrons is:\
\
-  less than the number of valence electrons the atom contributed to the total, the charge is positive.\
\
-  greater than the number of valence electrons the atom contributed to the total, the charge is negative.\
